Cybersecurity in the modern world

What exactly is cybersecurity?

Cybersecurity is the surveillance and control of data, software and the physical world by the central authority or the cybernetic body of a national state. Cybersecurity is also the control of information and communication (computer networks, cloud computing systems, etc.) or technology and information systems (information transfer networks or other electronic or physical networks).

Cybersecurity is an important part of the security of information technology and technology.
